# Testing environment

Before running, building, or reasoning about any MoQ ⇄ MPEG-TS test in this project,
**always read `INSTRUCTIONS.local.md` in the project root first.** It holds the raw,
machine-specific details that are deliberately kept out of Git:

- local relay server address/ports and the exact start command (incl. the
  `--server-quic-gso=false` and `https://` + `--client-tls-fingerprint` gotchas);
- repository paths, branch/commit under test, and how to locate the freshly-built
  binaries (the `cargo` target dir is redirected — `~/moq-dev/target/release` is stale);
- `mpegts-pacer` build + invocation;
- local test data (`~/*.ts` source clips) and the test-runner scripts (`~/t7-p1/…`);
- analysis tooling (TSDuck, `compliance.py`) and the measured P1 baselines;
- the remote EC2 path (IP, ports, SSH target, systemd services).

`INSTRUCTIONS.local.md` (and any `.env.local`) are git-ignored — do not commit them and
do not copy their raw IPs/paths/fingerprints into tracked files. When environment facts
change (rebuilds, new commit, new relay address, new clips), update
`INSTRUCTIONS.local.md` so it stays the single source of truth for local execution.
